{{Infobox person | name = Alan Nebauer | image = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Australia]] | nationality = [[Australia|Australian]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Sailor and author | known_for = BOC Challenge 1994 participation, rescue of competitor [[Josh Hall (sailor)|Josh Hall]] | website = }}
'''Alan Nebauer''' is an Australian yachtsman who competed in the [[Single-handed sailing|single-handed]] round-the-world [[Velux 5 Oceans Race#The BOC Challenge 1994–95|1994–95 BOC Challenge race]] aboard the yacht ''Newcastle Australia''.<ref>[http://www.velux5oceans.com/da/19942 ''Roll of Honour (1994)''], from the official web site {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060312172156/http://www.velux5oceans.com/da/19942|date=March 12, 2006}}</ref><ref>[http://www.solocircumnavigation.com/SoloAroundTheWorldRaces/BOC_And_AA_Races/BOC94_95/bocchallenge19941995results.htm ''The BOC Challenge 1994–1995 Results''], from solocircumnavigation.com</ref> Nebauer won two awards for his seamanship during the race<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/alan-nebauer/against-all-odds-3/|title=AGAINST ALL ODDS by Alan Nebauer|last=|first=|publisher=Kirkus Reviews|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en-us}}</ref>, one of them for rescuing his British competitor [[Josh Hall (sailor)|Josh Hall]], whose vessel foundered during the first leg from [[Charleston, South Carolina|Charleston]] to [[Cape Town]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/10/25/sports/alone-in-a-sea-of-trouble-boc-yacht-race-rescue-came-while-the-boat-was-sinking.html|title=Alone in a Sea of Trouble; BOC Yacht-Race Rescue Came While the Boat Was Sinking|last=Lloyd|first=Barbara|date=1994-10-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en}}</ref>
Nebauer wrote a book about his adventures in the race ({{Cite book|title=Against All Odds: around alone in the BOC challenge|last=|first=|publisher=McGraw Hill|year=1996|isbn=978-0-07-470331-1|location=|pages=|quote=|via=}}) and a documentary film was also produced.<ref>https://bennettmarine.com/products/against-the-odds-boc-challenge-1994-1995</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.screenaustralia.gov.au/the-screen-guide/t/against-the-odds-1995/9970|title=Against The Odds (1995) - Screen Australia|last=|first=|date=|website=www.screenaustralia.gov.au|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-05-23}}</ref>
Alan Nebauer and his wife, Cindy, currently run a charter business in [[Jervis Bay]], Australia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jervisbaysailingcharters.com.au/index.html#about-us|title=Jervis Bay Sailing Charters|website=www.jervisbaysailingcharters.com.au|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-23}}</ref>. Alan also remains involved with various yachting projects as a consultant and contract skipper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalprojectsyachting.com.au/|title=Worldwide Yacht Delivery {{!}} Yachting Project Management|website=www.globalprojectsyachting.com.au|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-23}}</ref>
