{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2011}} {{Infobox institute |name = European Energy Centre |image = [[File:EEC logo.gif|180px]] |image_size = 120px |image_name = |image_alt = |caption = |established = 2010; 1975 with Centro Studi Galileo |president = |chairman = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |staff = |budget = |endowment = |debt = |members = |location = |city = [[Edinburgh]], Scotland |state = |province = |country = United Kingdom |free_label = Other branches |free = Centro Studi Galileo [[Milan]], [[Casale Monferrato]], Rome, [[Padova]], [[Genova]], [[Bari]] ([[Italy]]), [[Pune]] ([[India]]) |coor = |address = |website = [http://www.EUenergycentre.org www.EUenergycentre.org] |footnotes = }}
The '''European Energy Centre''' (EEC) was incorporated in 2010 in Scotland as a private limited company<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/SC371195 |title=Companies House websearch |accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref>; it has no official links to the European Union. Although its website makes a claim that it was created in 1975, this relates to the Centro Studi Galileo, an affiliated (but legally unconnected) company in Italy that runs a biennial conference on air-conditioning and refrigeration. EEC's focus is on renewable energy training and conference delivery to help develop a workforce capable of installing, repairing and maintaining renewable energy equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euenergycentre.org/training |title=Renewable Energy Training |publisher=Euenergycentre.org |date= |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref>
The European Energy Centre and Centro Studi Galileo work with the [[United Nations Environment Programme]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unep.fr/ozonaction/information/mmc/lib_detail.asp?r=5257 |title=Magazine produced by the Centro Studi Galileo in cooperation with UNEP's OzonAction Programme |publisher=Unep.fr |date= |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref><ref>http://www.unep.fr/ozonaction/information/mmcfiles/6241-e-industria_formazione_special_issue_2.pdf</ref> (UNEP)<ref name="uneptie1">{{cite web|url=http://www.uneptie.org/ozonaction/events/Milan%20Conference%208-9%20June.pdf |title=Past conference organised by Centro Studi Galileo with the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> the Intergovernmental International Institute of Refrigeration<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iifiir.org/en/web-files.php?rub=1 |title=Cooperations between Centro Studi Galileo, United Nations Environment Programme and intergovernmental Institute of Refrigeration, technical publications in refrigeration and air conditioning |publisher=Iifiir.org |date= |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> and Centro Studi Galileo,<ref>{{cite web|author=Paolo Buoni |url=http://www.centrogalileo.it |title=Centro Studi Galileo |publisher=Centrogalileo.it |date=24 September 2007 |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> along with Universities such as [[Edinburgh Napier University]] and [[Heriot-Watt University]] in promoting the use of renewable energy technologies across the United Kingdom.
The European Energy Centre is also active European-wide<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.solarthermalworld.org/node/1146 |title=Global Solar Thermal Energy Council works with the European Energy Centre to promote adoption of renewable energy European-wide |publisher=Solarthermalworld.org |date=26 March 2010 |accessdate=24 April 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225224633/http://www.solarthermalworld.org/node/1146 |archivedate=25 February 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> with conferences in refrigeration, air conditioning and renewable energy, specifically Heating and Cooling technologies, see the 14th European Conference at [[Heriot-Watt University]], Edinburgh.<ref>[http://www.fluorocarbons.org/documents/Coming%20Events/14th%20Conference%20Edinburgh.pdf "14th European Conference organized by the intergovernmental Institute of Refrigeration"], the United Nations Environment Programme, the European Energy Centre (EEC) and Centro Studi Galileo</ref>
The European Energy Centre is also active in India with training courses and conferences<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/on-earth-day-workshops-on-renewable-energy/610257/1 |title=Newspaper article from the Indian Express, Renewable Energy training courses and conferences by the European Energy Centre in India |work=The Indian Express |location=India |date=23 April 2010 |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> with its Indian Partner TERRE Policy Centre.
==Main activities of the organisation==
*European conferences organised with the UN (UNEP) on the latest technologies in renewable energy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.scotsman.com/news/City-university-to-host-UN.6590540.jp |title=Example of national newspaper talking about the conference launched by the EEC with the United Nations Environment Programme on the 21 January 2011 at Heriot-Watt University in Edinburgh on The Latest Technologies in Renewable Energy |work= The Scotsman. |date= |accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> *Publications with the [[United Nations Environment Programme]] *Promotion of best practices in renewable energy through training technicians and personnel *Launching the [[Green New Deal]] in Europe and India
