{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} [[File:NL-Nationaleparken.svg|thumb|right|National Parks in the Netherlands]] '''[[National park]]s in the [[Netherlands]]''' were defined in the 1960s as areas of at least 10&nbsp;km² consisting of natural terrains, water and/or forests, with a special landscape and flora and fauna.
The first two national parks were founded in the 1930s by private organisations. The first official national park, [[Schiermonnikoog National Park]], was not established until 1989. The most recent national park to have been established is the [[Nieuw Land National Park]], which is established in 2018.
In 2011, the government decided to make the provinces responsible for the national parks.
